  "2026-05-24T23:55:54.552Z",codex-docs-dedupe-lane,"Evidence from docs/plugin single-source lane (read-only, 2026-05-25): actual Claude plugin inventory from files is plugins/pm-claude/.claude-plugin/plugin.json + .mcp.json + hooks/hooks.json/session-start.mjs, 14 slash command files, 5 skill files, 4 agent files, script launcher, README. Actual MCP server source exposes 18 tools: pm_run plus 17 narrow tools including pm_plan. Drift found: docs/CLAUDE_CODE_PLUGIN.md architecture tree and install section still say 9 slash commands and one agent/coordination surface, while plugins/pm-claude/README.md says 14 slash commands and lists all 14 command files. README says \"3 subagents\" but lists 4 agent files and plugin.json description also says 3. scripts/smoke-claude-plugin.mjs is stale too: comments say 18 required tools and 9 commands, but the required MCP list omits pm_plan and the pluginFiles array only checks 9 command files plus one agent; it can pass while docs drift. Recommendation: make plugins/pm-claude/README.md the canonical user-facing capability inventory because it is closest to install/user surface; make docs/CLAUDE_CODE_PLUGIN.md the architecture/testing page and either route capability counts to README or replace the static tree with a compact \"inventory comes from files under plugins/pm-claude/{commands,skills,agents}\" note. Smallest edit: update counts to 14 commands/5 skills/4 agents wherever counts remain, or avoid counts outside the canonical README; fix smoke script metadata/checks to enumerate all current command and agent files and include pm_plan in required tools.\n"
